parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
unusual noises from the engine
knocking or grinding sounds
oil leaks
smoke or burning smells
difficulty accelerating
rough idling
and shaking engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil system failure can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or engine replacement.
symptoms: Oil leaks
low oil pressure
oil burning or consumption
metal shavings in the oil
unusual noises from the engine
knocking or grinding sounds
smoke or burning smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving on highways, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power while driving
the vehicle slows down or comes to a complete stop
the power steering and brakes may not function
the dashboard may go dark
and the vehicle may shut off suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or hesitates to shift gears
the vehicle accelerates on its own
and the transmission may transfer gears unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption and engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or catch fire, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the engine may shut off or stall
and the vehicle may catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate suddenly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
especially when driving at high speeds
and the vehicle may transfer gears unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable acceleration and deceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to respond to acceleration
shuts off unexpectedly
and has a loud knocking sound accompanied by sluggish driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can lead to theft and unauthorized access to the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle is easily broken into due to the lack of proper ignition safeguards.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to accidents and injuries due to the inability to alert other drivers or pedestrians.
symptoms: The horn works intermittently or not at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the loss of critical vehicle functions.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences weird noises
lights turning on and off
and the car sounds like it wants to shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The engine catches fire
shuts off unexpectedly
and has a ticking sound coming from the computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to reduced visibility.
symptoms: The headlights flicker or cut off and on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the rapid spread of fire.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire due to an electrical fault
resulting in a complete loss of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brake lights stop working
and the vehicle experiences multiple instrumentation failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
and all the lights on the instrument panel illuminate.
